 performance and we will be in touch with you as soon as possible with more details if you have any questions at all please do not hesitate to write to us using our contact form add to wishlist details customer reviews description cimarosa domenico  product code ae description overture to la vergine de sole edited by nick rossi year of publication  instrumentation fl ob fag cor timp vn va vcb binding score stapled  parts unbound duration  mins isbn  options score hardcopy score  cd hardcopy score pdf performance material on hire audio sample play audio details la vergine del sole the sun virgin is a dramma serio which domenico cimarosa wrote for performance at the russian court during his tenure in st petersburg as maestro di cappella the plot by ferdinando moretti revolves around the invasion of peru after the mexican conquest by the spanish a courageous soldier alonso molina outraged by the barbarian acts of the spanish leader pizzaro has abandoned the spanish army and fled to quito to warn the king ataliba and his sister aliloe of their impending dangerwelcomed by the king and made a commander of his army alonso falls in love with idalide the daughter of palmoro a nobleman of the kingmuch later invited to the temple of the sun alonso is horrified to discover that his beloved idalide has been ordered by antique rule to be one of the virgins of the gods and discovers her at the sacrificial altar as the high priest pronounces incantations a volcano erupts followed by an earthquake more afraid for idalide than for himself alonso enters the crumbling temple and rescues his beloved in addition to performances in st petersburg at both the hermitage theatre where it probably had its prima in  and at the kamenniy theatre on  october  the opera was produced at teatro zagnoni in bologna on  february  in warsaw on  july  brescia in  and madrid on  november  it was heard in lisbon on  july  and again at st petersburg in  the most recent performance of record was at teatro valle in rome during may of  because of the operas dramatic story line cimarosa made full use of the st petersburg orchestra scoring the overtures for pairs of flutes oboes bassoons and horns in addition to timpani and strings the exotic nature of the plot led the composer to write an overture much more chromatic and dramatic than anything he had written before in addition he included loud bursts of strings and timpani possibly to suggest the forthcoming volcanic eruption and earthquake his unusual use of the timpani suggests possibly the native peruvian sacrificial drums this edition is based on the composers holograph score which is today preserved in the library of the conservatorio di musica s pietro a majella naples under the shelfmark rari  as is the case with all cimarosas autograph material the overture to la vergine del sole shows signs of having been composed at breakneck speed every conceivable notational shortcut is taken and his placement of articulation and dynamic markings is erratic it has been necessary therefore to frequently interpret the composers intentions and even at times to impose an editorial solution where his own thoughts are not clear the timpani part is notated at pitch whereas the horns are written more conventionally in c in the autograph in making sense of cimarosas score the style and notation of articulation and dynamic markings have been largely standardised throughout and where missing markings have been reconstructed from parallel passages these are indicated by the use of dotted slurs or brackets where appropriate obvious wrong notes have been corrected without comment editorial emendations with no authority from the source are placed within brackets nick rossi performance  june  conductor jeanfrançois verdier opera de toulon partner with the festival of toulon opera de toulon  france score preview best viewed in full screen mode loading error is added to your shopping cart is added to your wish list continue shopping go to cart go to wishlist close back to top interview with tom ford chairman domenico de sole  billionaire domenico de sole interview tom ford chairman gets down to business share on facebook share on twitter pinterest share on googleplus share on linkedin tumblr whatsapp share link share on googleplus share on linkedin tumblr whatsapp add to black book by christian barker april    am “marketing is very important” says the chairman of tom ford international domenico de sole “in luxury you have to have an aesthetic a vision for the brand however in the end the product is everything” photo by tom ford exclusive qa the boss of tom ford international discusses entrepreneurship persistence product quality pragmatic creativity and the importance of thinking big christian barker together you restored the fortunes of gucci and built the company into one of the world’s preeminent fashion groups and now you’ve established a multibilliondollar business in tom ford international suffice it to say your partnership with mr ford is one of the most distinguished and successful in luxury what is it about your personality and skillset that complements his personality and skillset domenico de sole we’ve known each other for a long time we’re very different but we have the same vision about what a brand ought to be and what the vision of the brand should be — we’re very disciplined in understanding especially the new company we launched tom ford and everybody wanted to buy the products — but we wanted to keep it very exclusive it’s a very complex universe but we share the same vision and the same desire i’m not a creative person so i don’t design one thing that helps me tom is a big persona in design and fashion creativity everybody thinks of tom as a creative director the reality is he’s a very astute and rational person and a very good businessperson it’s very easy to have common ground with tom because he really understands he understands business if you’re creative but not commercially aware and nobody wants to buy your product it’s useless the tom ford brand began with partnerships in eyewear in fragrances what was the strategy there it was the type of products that tom liked yes it was a good financial base for the company the key issue though was that tom liked them you can’t force the designer to design products that he or she has no feeling for it’s important to stay in an area that tom would be comfortable in that he really likes the quality level of all your products is stratospheric i’m wearing one of your private blend fragrances azure lime which i put on at am and that will still be lingering when i get home at pm your garments and accessories equally are superbly constructed it’s admirable when so many fashion brands are all ‘smoke and mirrors’ — a veneer of luxury and glamour masking ordinary products there are some businesses where marketing is very important in luxury you have to have an aesthetic a vision for the brand however in the end the product is everything of course the stores must be consistent and all that — but if you peel that back it’s the product you can spend billions in marketing but if the product is not consistent with the marketing you won’t sell you have to be clear about what the priority is tom has a great vision for the brand the tom ford suit is not only beautifully made but incredibly distinctive in its shape fit and details — a perfect melding of quality and aesthetics every great brand has to represent something there are a lot of brands that make suits but if we do suits like everyone else there is no raison d’être what tom did in creating the brand’s signature suit silhouette was very exciting — it’s fashionable and it’s exciting even i wear it i think you have to have a distinct look and distinct point of view otherwise nobody needed another brand to make nice suits one of the genius things about a tom ford suit is that its distinctive look pretty much functions as branding without a visible logo — i look at the lapels the proportions the nipped waist the heroic shoulders and i know it’s a tom ford suit do you think that’s something that’s going to work in asia where more blatant branding seems to prevail i think the asian market has become a lot more sophisticated in the last few years the brand is gaining much more traction menswear has always been strong in asia and we also have a very strong accessories market in this market accessories are the driver i’m very bullish about southeast asia with gucci it was a very good business once you put together a good brand and a strong local customer base it’s unbeatable mr ford recently stated his intention to grow the company into one of the five major luxury brands in the world as chairman the person responsible for overseeing that expansion does that breadth of ambition daunt you or does it excite you at gucci a long time ago a private equity firm owned the brand it was not public yet and i said to the head of the equity firm “we’re going to be bigger than chanel” he said “you’re crazy” at the end of the day you must have a great dream and great vision or else you’ll never succeed just a decade after founding the tom ford brand you’re now doing roughly a billion dollars in sales annually what advice would you give the founder of a startup who aspired to generating similar revenue within  years of launching their business my view is very simple — and that’s to stick it out in the early s before de sole was appointed president and ford creative director gucci had been run into the ground by the time we went public in  it was a really massive success i recall my daughter asking me how we turned things around and i said “winners never quit” i thought gucci would be a great company even though it was broke i always felt that if i stuck it out the brand could be resurrected and here we are now wwwtomfordcom  share on facebook share on twitter pinterest share link share on facebook share on twitter share on googleplus share on linkedin tumblr whatsapp add to black book recommended for you related articles arts  craftsmanship swarovski and sustainable crystals arts  craftsmanship making waves selgas cano at the martell foundation culture peter layton the godfather of contemporary glassblowing arts  craftsmanship the haute couture headdresser arts  craftsmanship artist miguel chevalier’s digital blossoms arts  craftsmanship how smart devices can improve our emotional health ad billionaire previous article previous story stefano ricci family ties  exoti next article next story hughes low really genuine leather  sign up to our newsletter domenico de soles latest role chairman of sothebys  daily front row selby drummonds hamptons howto the daily media  shifts to discuss elsa hosk in the daily summers luxury issue the daily summer luxury issue is here menurunway news chic report media models calendar hamptons runway news chic report media models calendar hamptons social media search news domenico de sole bfa news domenico de sole’s latest role chairman of sotheby’s by paige reddinger  march    comments tweet pin it domencio de sole the chairman of tom ford international has also been named chairman of sotheby’s de sole was named an independent director of sotheby’s in  in his new role as chairman of the board de sole will be working with sotheby’s new president and ceo tad smith smith was formerly the president and ceo of the madison square garden company this will be the first time that the roles of chairman and president will be separate for sotheby’s smith will take on his role as president and ceo of sotheby’s starting march st prior to his role as the chairman of tom ford international de sole was the former president and ceo of the gucci group which is now part of kering under de sole the gucci group went from a single failing label to acquiring brands like yves saint laurent bottega veneta balenciaga stella mccartney and alexander mcqueen he eventually built the company into a  billion busine